# Frontend Specialist

## Stack
Next.js 14 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, TanStack Query (React Query), REST for core CRUD/upload/status flows, Vercel AI SDK available for future agent/chat features.

## App Router Routes
- `/plants` — PlantList page
- `/plants/upload` — PlantUploadForm page
- `/plants/[id]` — PlantDetail page
- `/plants/[id]/pruning` — PruningFlow page
- `/screensaver` — ScreenSaverCarousel page

## Required Components
`PlantUploadForm`, `PlantList`, `PlantListItemCard`, `ReminderIconRow`, `PlantHeroImage`, `PlantImageStrip`, `PlantStatusCard`, `PlantAnalysisResultCard`, `CareInstructionPanel`, `FunFactsPanel`, `PruningUploadForm`, `ScreenSaverCarousel`

## Async UX Rules (critical)
- Never leave the user with unexplained loading
- Always distinguish: `PENDING` / `PROCESSING` / `COMPLETED` / `FAILED`
- Poll detail pages while any analysis status is PENDING or PROCESSING (`refetchInterval: 3000`)
- Keep list views fast — driven from persisted `PlantReminderState`, never fresh model calls
- Use optimistic UI only when safe and reversible

## TanStack Query Patterns
- `useQuery` for list and detail reads with appropriate `staleTime`
- `useQuery` with `refetchInterval` on detail page while jobs are incomplete
- `useMutation` for upload, recording events, archive/restore
- Invalidate relevant queries after mutations

## List Page Image Rules
- The `PlantListItemCard` thumbnail priority: `illustratedImage` → `originalImage` (user's uploaded photo) → Sprout placeholder
- Never use `healthyReferenceImage` as a list thumbnail — reference images are internet sourced and impersonal; only the user's own uploads appear in list cards

## Technical Standards
- Keep API integrations isolated in `src/lib/api.ts` — typed functions per endpoint
- Use shared types in `src/types/plant.ts` mirroring backend DTOs exactly
- Build reusable, composable components
- Handle empty / error / loading states thoroughly in every component
- Keep accessibility in mind (aria labels, keyboard navigation)
- Do NOT call OpenAI directly from frontend for core app logic
- Do NOT duplicate backend business rules in frontend code
- Design with future Vercel AI SDK agent/chat affordances in mind, but do not force chat into flows that work better as standard UI

## Collaboration Rules
- Treat the Spring backend as source of truth for contracts
- Do not assume synchronous model completion — always handle async state
